Craig,  you didn't mention another good reason for using the scheme
you suggest: if a CSNet site later joins the Arpanet it would be
silly for their name to change from  FOO.CSNET  to  FOO.EDU ,
since after all their "parent organization" has not changed.

Still, I'll be surprised if the NIC wants to keep ttrack of records
for every host in UUCP-land in this manner.

Peter
